================================================================
 FZPKG CATALOG - README 
 File: catalog.json
 Total packages: 99
================================================================

WHAT THIS IS

This is a JSON catalog of C/C++ open-source libraries and system
components of the ForgeZero infactructure.

WHO IS THIS FOR?
For FZ users and sys devs who need fast, reliable, and secure lib provisioning for their specific tasks - the package are automatically vendored into the config.

Tags marked "master" have no strict release tag upstream; pin
them to a specific commit before using in production.

IMPORTANT
If you would like to contribute and add your own library or any third-party package, please open a PR and include a link to package you with to add in the description so that we can review it.

================================================================
 KERNEL / OS
================================================================

linux        - The Linux kernel itself. Core of most embedded
               and server Linux systems.
busybox      - Single binary combining tiny versions of many
               standard UNIX command line tools (ls, mount,
               init, etc). Common in embedded Linux images.
FreeRTOS     - Small real-time OS kernel, most widely used RTOS
               for microcontrollers.
Zephyr       - Full-featured scalable RTOS from the Linux
               Foundation, supports many architectures.
RT-Thread    - RTOS popular in China, modular, POSIX-like API.
NuttX        - POSIX-compliant RTOS (Apache project), feels
               like a tiny embedded Linux.
systemd      - Linux init system and service manager, also
               provides logging (journald), udev, networkd.


================================================================
 BOOTLOADER
================================================================

u-boot       - "Das U-Boot", the most common bootloader for
               embedded ARM/RISC-V/MIPS boards.


================================================================
 IOT / VENDOR FRAMEWORKS
================================================================

esp-idf      - Espressif's official SDK for ESP32 family chips
               (WiFi/BLE microcontrollers).


================================================================
 HARDWARE ABSTRACTION / LOW LEVEL
================================================================

pico-sdk     - Official SDK for Raspberry Pi RP2040/RP2350 chips.
libopencm3   - Free firmware library for ARM Cortex-M
               microcontrollers (STM32, others).
CMSIS_6      - ARM's Cortex Microcontroller Software Interface
               Standard, common HAL layer for Cortex-M/A cores.
libgpiod     - Modern Linux GPIO access library (replaces the
               old sysfs GPIO interface).
pigpio       - GPIO control library for Raspberry Pi (also PWM,
               servo, waveform generation).


================================================================
 LIBC
================================================================

picolibc     - Small C library made for embedded systems
               (merged Newlib + avr-libc), low memory footprint.
musl         - Lightweight, fast, standards-compliant libc,
               popular for static binaries and Alpine Linux.


================================================================
 NETWORK
================================================================

lwip         - Lightweight TCP/IP stack for embedded systems
               with limited RAM.
curl         - The library behind the curl command, supports
               HTTP/FTP/and many other protocols.
mongoose     - Embedded web server / networking library, easy
               to embed in firmware.
civetweb     - Small embeddable HTTP server library.
kcp          - Fast reliable UDP-based protocol, low latency,
               used in games and real-time apps.
quiche       - Cloudflare's QUIC and HTTP/3 implementation.
libpcap      - Packet capture library, used by tcpdump/Wireshark
               and for writing network sniffers.
dpdk         - Data Plane Development Kit, kernel-bypass high
               performance packet processing.


================================================================
 ASYNC / EVENT LOOPS / CONCURRENCY
================================================================

libevent     - Portable async event notification library.
libuv        - Async I/O library, the engine behind Node.js.
libev        - Minimal high-performance event loop library.
concurrentqueue - Lock-free multi-producer multi-consumer queue
               for C++.
userspace-rcu - Read-Copy-Update synchronization for userspace,
               used for very low overhead concurrent reads.


================================================================
 CRYPTO / TLS
================================================================

mbedtls      - Small footprint TLS/crypto library, popular in
               embedded and IoT projects.
wolfssl      - Lightweight embedded TLS library, alternative
               to mbedTLS/OpenSSL.
openssl      - The most widely used general purpose TLS/crypto
               library.
libsodium    - Modern, easy-to-use crypto library (based on
               NaCl), good default choice for new projects.
liboqs       - Post-quantum cryptography algorithms, for
               future-proofing against quantum computers.


================================================================
 SERIALIZATION
================================================================

protobuf-c   - Protocol Buffers implementation for plain C.
nanopb       - Very small Protocol Buffers implementation,
               made for microcontrollers.
protobuf     - Google's Protocol Buffers, main C++/multi-lang
               implementation.
flatbuffers  - Zero-copy serialization format, good for games
               and high performance apps.
msgpack-c    - MessagePack binary serialization for C/C++.
tinycbor     - Small CBOR (binary JSON-like format) encoder
               and decoder.


================================================================
 JSON / CONFIG FORMATS
================================================================

cJSON        - Lightweight JSON parser/writer in plain C,
               very common in embedded projects.
yyjson       - Extremely fast JSON library for C.
jsmn         - Minimal JSON tokenizer, no allocations.
tomlc99      - TOML config file parser for C99.
inih         - Simple .ini config file parser.
yaml         - libyaml, YAML parser and emitter for C.


================================================================
 COMPRESSION
================================================================

zlib         - The classic DEFLATE compression library, used
               almost everywhere.
zstd         - Facebook's Zstandard, fast modern compression
               with high ratio.
lz4          - Extremely fast compression, low ratio, good for
               real-time use cases.
brotli       - Google's compression algorithm, used a lot on
               the web (better ratio than gzip).


================================================================
 IMAGE / GUI / TEXT
================================================================

libpng       - Reference library for reading/writing PNG images.
libjpeg-turbo - Fast JPEG codec (SIMD-optimized libjpeg fork).
stb          - Single-header public domain libraries for image
               loading, fonts, etc (stb_image and friends).
lvgl         - Popular embedded graphics library for building
               UI on microcontrollers with a display.
freetype     - Font rendering engine, renders TrueType/OpenType
               fonts.
harfbuzz     - Text shaping engine, works together with
               FreeType for complex scripts.


================================================================
 AUDIO / VIDEO
================================================================

PortAudio    - Cross-platform audio I/O library.
libsndfile   - Library for reading/writing audio files (WAV,
               FLAC, etc).
opus         - Modern low-latency audio codec, used in VoIP
               and streaming.
FFmpeg       - The universal multimedia framework: decode,
               encode, transcode, stream almost any format.


================================================================
 MATH
================================================================

Eigen        - C++ template library for linear algebra
               (matrices, vectors, solvers).
cglm         - Fast C library for graphics math (vectors,
               matrices, quaternions), OpenGL/Vulkan friendly.


================================================================
 DATABASE
================================================================

sqlite       - Self-contained, serverless, embedded SQL
               database engine, extremely widely used.
hiredis      - Minimalistic C client library for Redis.


================================================================
 FILESYSTEM
================================================================

littlefs     - Fail-safe filesystem for embedded flash storage,
               designed to survive power loss.
FatFs        - Generic FAT filesystem module for small
               embedded systems.
spiffs       - SPI Flash File System, made for small embedded
               flash chips.


================================================================
 USB
================================================================

tinyusb      - Open source cross-platform USB host/device stack
               for embedded systems.
libusb       - Cross-platform library for USB device access
               from userspace (host side).
hidapi       - Simple library for talking to USB and Bluetooth
               HID devices.


================================================================
 MESSAGING / RPC
================================================================

mosquitto    - Popular open source MQTT broker.
paho.mqtt.c  - Eclipse Paho MQTT client library in C.
libcoap      - CoAP protocol library, lightweight alternative
               to HTTP for constrained devices.
libzmq       - ZeroMQ, high performance asynchronous messaging
               library.
nng          - nanomsg-next-gen, lightweight messaging library,
               successor to nanomsg.
grpc         - Google's RPC framework, works over HTTP/2 with
               Protocol Buffers.


================================================================
 INDUSTRIAL / FIELDBUS
================================================================

libmodbus    - C library implementing the Modbus protocol,
               common in industrial automation.
can-utils    - Linux userspace utilities for CAN bus (used in
               automotive and industrial systems).


================================================================
 IPC
================================================================

dbus         - Desktop Bus, standard Linux inter-process
               communication system.


================================================================
 STORAGE (HIGH PERFORMANCE)
================================================================

spdk         - Storage Performance Development Kit, kernel
               bypass NVMe/storage acceleration framework.


================================================================
 MEMORY ALLOCATORS
================================================================

jemalloc     - General purpose malloc implementation with good
               multi-threaded performance, used by Meta/Redis.
mimalloc     - Microsoft's fast, small footprint malloc
               replacement.
tlsf         - Two-Level Segregated Fit allocator, O(1)
               allocation, popular in embedded/real-time systems.


================================================================
 LOGGING
================================================================

spdlog       - Fast C++ logging library, header-only or compiled.
liblog4c     - log4j-style logging library for C.


================================================================
 STRING FORMATTING
================================================================

fmt          - Modern, fast, type-safe string formatting
               library for C++ (basis of C++20 std::format).


================================================================
 TESTING
================================================================

Catch2       - Modern C++ unit testing framework, simple syntax.
googletest   - Google's C++ testing framework, very widely used.
Unity        - Lightweight C unit testing framework, made for
               embedded targets.
cmocka       - Unit testing framework for C with mocking support.
doctest      - Extremely lightweight single-header C++ test
               framework.
benchmark    - Google's microbenchmarking library for C++.


================================================================
 DEBUGGING
================================================================

OpenOCD      - On-Chip Debugger, connects to JTAG/SWD hardware
               for flashing and debugging microcontrollers.
tracy        - Real-time, nanosecond-resolution frame profiler
               for C/C++ applications and games.


================================================================
 GENERAL UTILITIES
================================================================

uthash       - Header-only hash table and linked list macros
               for plain C structs.
klib         - Collection of lightweight generic C containers
               and algorithms (hash maps, sorting, etc).
etl          - Embedded Template Library, STL-like containers
               that avoid dynamic memory allocation.
argparse     - Command line argument parsing library for C++.
CLI11        - Feature-rich command line parser for modern C++.


================================================================
 NOTES
================================================================

- If you are unsure about a particular package, please verify it directly on GitHub. You are solely responsible for any packages downloaded from catalog.json(fz pm catalog); we merely provide a convenient installation mechanism. There are you no hidden secrets or, worse, fraudulent content - all package data is current as of 2026. 

